headline: Carnival, Norwegian Cruise Line, Sabre, Lindblad Expeditions, and Warner Bros. Discovery Shares Skyrocket, What You Need To Know
summary: A number of stocks jumped in the afternoon session after the major indices rebounded (Nasdaq +2.0%, S&P 500 +1.5%) as President Trump postponed the planned 50% tariff on European Union imports, shifting the start date to July 9, 2025.

headline: CCL vs. NCLH: Which Cruise Stock Offers Smoother Sailing in 2025?
summary: CCL rides strong bookings, yield growth and debt cuts to lead cruise stocks, while NCLH lags with lower earnings momentum and rising leverage.
